  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "About this dashboard",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 4
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**Model Performance & Usefulness** \u2014 how the cascade's models did across this repo's tested scenarios (the 5 Kathirmani cameras \u00d7 Marlin/Locate/Qwen, fed from `results/*.json` via `serve_metrics.py`).\n\n- **Usefulness** = did the model produce signal worth acting on: events found, find-query parse success, Qwen loss-prevention signals, cross-camera dedup, and events per watt-hour.\n- **Performance** = what it cost to get there: inference time, per-camera latency, GPU utilization/power, unified memory, energy and \u20b9.\n\nSource of truth is `results/*.json`; data persists between runs via `serve_metrics.py` (`bash start_stack.sh`). See `spec/10`/`spec/11` for the platform's model dashboards 11\u201318."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Total events",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4,
        "w": 4,
        "h": 4
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "marlin-metrics"
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calc": "lastNotNull",
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "textMode": "auto"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "none",
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "marlin_total_events",
          "legendFormat": "events",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "marlin-metrics"
